race.comment: BIG SISTER AVA (10) looks the one to beat off a strong debut showing at Kilmore when well supported in the market there and working home well for a narrow second. She'll be fitter and better for that and maps for every chance from the soft gate. EPOCH (2) has been solid in two runs back over shorter trips and looks suited getting to a mile third up. He can roll forward and stay the trip well. SIAM EMERALD (6) ran well fresh at Echuca over 1400m, an improvement on his form last time in. He can improve off that. FOUR CANDLES (3) was solid first up at Pakenham and should relish getting to this trip now.
